0 @S1@ SOUR
1 TITL O'Malley Family Bible
1 AUTH Various family members
1 NOTE Contains photographs (Gerald & Mary O'Malley as children, captioned "Gerald 5 yrs old, Mary 3 yr."), letters, newspaper clippings, handwritten family trees on Tube-Tex notepads, church study questions, and Gerald O'Malley's church membership card (Easter Sunday, April 9, 1950). Family history information copied from Thelma's bible by Millie O'Malley. Obituary of Dan Cotton enclosed, sent by Mrs. Ralph A. Baker (Laura Baker) in June 1991.

0 @S2@ SOUR
1 TITL Letter from Johnny D. Walker
1 AUTH Johnny D. Walker
1 DATE 24 DEC 1980
1 NOTE Letter to Mrs. Gerald L. O'Malley, 425 Light Street, Dyersburg, TN, researching Segraves family connection. Walker is descended from Sherrod Segraves through the Smith line. Was referred by Mrs. A.H. (Martha) Bledsoe. Found in O'Malley Family Bible.

0 @S3@ SOUR
1 TITL Letter from Millie O'Malley
1 AUTH Millie O'Malley
1 DATE 22 AUG 1991
1 NOTE Letter from Millie E. O'Malley, RR 6 Box 92, Oswego, NY 13126, to Mr. & Mrs. Gerald O'Malley. Enclosed typed family history information copied from Thelma's bible. Note: Millie's document contains two known errors — lists Gerald and Emma Ruth's wedding as 12/28/1936 (correct: 12/28/1934) and Patricia's birth as 4/2/1938 (correct: 4/2/1937). Found in O'Malley Family Bible.

0 @S4@ SOUR
1 TITL Newspaper Obituary - Dan Cotton
1 DATE 26 FEB 1931
1 NOTE Newspaper obituary headlined "DAN COTTON DIES EARLY THURSDAY", dated 2-24-31. Sent to Mrs. Gerald O'Malley by Mrs. Ralph A. Baker (Laura Baker) on June 28, 1991, who found it going through some of Ralph's papers. Funeral home: J. W. Curry and Son. Found in O'Malley Family Bible.

